Moosesian race

races.description: The Half-Dragons have been a space faring race for quite a long time, contrary to popular belief these noble yet somewhat savage folk are not genetically engineered. They are easily spotted by their physical differences with humans thanks to their colorful scales, draconic eyes, horns and even tails! Thanks to their physical differences and strong scales people of this race proved themselves to be excellent melee combatants. It was easy to find them serving various empires outside of their own as front line fighters. Sadly due to their hardy nature and exotic looks many Half-Dragons end up captured and forced into gladiatorial combat. There are other reasons they are highly sought after; unique biological traits that are wholly unique to them. One of which allows to combine a specialized ore with their blood that activates various powerful abilities. A point of debate of many scholars is how such a openly savage race had made it to spaceflight, much less a force that roams about the galaxy. This is in large part thanks to a rare sub group of Half-Dragons that lead their kind in political, cultural and scientific endeavors. These "albino's" are almost the polar opposites of their more common brutish brethren. Despite a strong imperial nation and a sense of loyalty to their own, those that find themselves able to escape their gladiatorial slavery often form up as pirates. These pirates tend to be ruthless and a general nuisance in the galaxy. Half dragons
races.name: Half dragon

races.description: It is a human like a rodent gene. Although the origin is unknown, it is a monarchy society based on agricultural society. There are more female objects than males, and it is difficult to distinguish the gender of the object when viewed from the outside. NewRatkinPlus

Descendants of glitterworld explorers who settled in the deep sea, generations of body modifications has led to their current form. Spreading far and wide into the rim, they built many cities and prospered. Until now. Moyo-From the depth
races.name: Moyo

races.description: These creatures resemble human females with extensive cybernetic augments, but they are actually physical manifestations of warship personas. They are created by channeling the untapped psychic energies of the collective unconscious to acheive unparaleled firepower miniaturization, at a cost of giving them somewhat eclectic personalities and appearances. Be aware that loading them down with heavy cannons and armor with lower their movement ability and amplify their prodigious appetites. They often resemble tribal deities, colorful pop stars, or historical figures whose names they bear. Ship Girl Race
races.name: Ship Girl

races.description: The legacy of a fallen empire, with a distant link to the humanoid races of earth and beyond. Other than the fact that they began to awaken over the past century, no one knows much else about what they are, where they are from or fundamentals behind their technology, which seems to bridge the gap between science and magic. Forsakens
races.name: forsaken

races.description: A holographic projection operated by a mind located elsewhere. Despite its humanlike appearance, the avatar could belong to a machine persona with frighteningly alien goals. If the projection is destroyed, its emitter will need a day to reestablish coherence, but the mind itself suffers no permanent harm. Save Our Ship 2
races.name: machine avatar

races.description: The geth are a race of networked artificial intelligences that reside beyond the Perseus Veil. The geth were created by the quarians as laborers and tools of war. When the geth became sentient and began to question their masters, the quarians attempted to exterminate them. Mass Effect - Playable Geth

races.name: M7 Mechanised infantry

races.description: A prototype M7 mechanized infantry, equipped with a limited SkyCore unit and SkyMind radio. These units are very strong, powerful war machines and allow digital consciousness to move on battlefields but are subsequently slow and have limited internal storage capacity to them. Android tiers
races.name: M8 Mechanised infantry

races.description: A lost android, shunned from their transcendant community. The tech used to make them is beyond human comprehension, boasting near unlimited power and requiring little sustinence to operate. They deem all races other than themselves to be somewhat below them and believe that living on a rimworld is a fate worse than death. Android tiers
races.name: T5 Android

races.description: The most advanced form of android conceivable; this tier is able to efficiently hold the consciousness of any AI uploaded onto it, with advanced locomotive abilities and manipulation; this android vastly suprasses most humans. Android tiers
races.name: T4 Android

races.description: A Prototype android exclusive to this rimworld; developed by a secret R/D Laboratory, away from the eye of the rest of the planet and cosmos. This android features highly advanced locomotive and motor abilities, perfectly mimicing that of an average human. Although clunky and somewhat slow - this android features a modular component design, allowing for upgrades to be made to current parts at any point. Android tiers
races.name: T3 Android

races.description: As simple as sentient robotics can get. This design is the bare skeletal amount of components needed to create full autonomous functionality. Obviously not the best but it works well when needed. Android tiers
races.name: T1 Android

races.description: A somewhat advanced android, capable of almost perfectly storing an AI consciousness and with reasonable levels of motor skills. A good all round android that is uses extensively on glitterworlds for basic maintenance and cleaning. Android tiers
races.name: T2 Android

races.description: A reclusive and diminishing race of proto-mechanical persona, 'skeletons' are fully sentient and feeling mechanical entities; they were built thousands of years ago as stand-ins for humans during lengthy processes, such as space flight. Since being manufactured they have been replaced by the far more complex mechanoid and AI persona. They have no fear of prejudice or fear of death - and are usually levelheaded thinkers. Being mechanical in nature - 'skeletons' do not need sustenance or rest, but this does not make them invulnerable to "pain" signals, chemical signals, or psychic engines. Furthermore, due to their incredibly long lifespan and common crushing existential dread; most 'skeletons' are depressed or dreadfully pessimistic of their future. Rim-Skeletons
races.name: skeleton

races.description: A robotic maid with a simple AI, for all your housekeeping needs! Robot Maid
races.name: RobotMaid

races.description: The krogan are a species of large reptilian bipeds native to the planet Tuchanka, a world known for its harsh environments, scarce resources, and overabundance of vicious predators. Bob's Mass Effect Krogans
races.name: Krogan

races.description: The most distinguishing feature of turians is their metallic carapace. The turians evolved this trait as a defense against the greater levels of solar radiation that penetrate their homeworld's weak magnetic field. Bob's Mass Effect Turians
races.name: Turian

data.mod: RimEffect - Asari of the Rims Continued [1.1][1.2]

races.description: A mono-gender race, the asari are distinctly feminine in appearance and possess maternal instincts. Their unique physiology, expressed in a millennium-long lifespan and the ability to reproduce with a partner of any gender or species, gives them a conservative yet convivial attitude toward other races. RimEffect - Asari of the Rims Continued (1.1)(1.2)
races.name: asari

races.description: Inhabitants of lunar cities that carry the genes of rabbits, the rabbie excel at waging war and constructing mega-cities. They travel the galaxy in search of celestial bodies with planetarium; a drug that the rabbie population has been reliant on for survival since the begining of their history. It is believed they originally came from another galaxy, but have sinced lost the technology and have been cut off from their home galaxy. Rabbie The Moonrabbit race
races.name: Rabbie

races.description: A Xenohuman hailing from a luxurious Glitterworld, genetically modified to enhance charisma, intellect, and to satisfy an odd, bygone fashion trend. This particular Glitterworlder seems to be encrusted in decorative 'gemstones', though the stones are little more than polished calcium deposits grown naturally by their body. Xenohumans Expanded
races.name: glitterworld human

races.description: A Xenohuman whose biology seems to have stemmed from evolutionary adaptations to high-gravity planets. They are quite short, but their strength is unmatched by most. However, their intellectual prowess, or rather lack thereof, is less than impressive. Xenohumans Expanded
races.name: gravity dwarf

races.description: A Xenohuman originating from a planet with significantly lower gravity than usual. Over time, their metabolic resources seem to have redistributed more towards brain development than managing atrophy. As such, they are physically frail but superior to most others intellectually. Xenohumans Expanded
races.name: lo-grav human

races.description: A Xenohuman descendant from surviving denizens of a toxic Radworld. Their immune system has adapted over time to foreign chemical and radiological hazards, making them nigh-immune to diseases and infections. Appearance, it seems, was left by the wayside, and they are quite hideous to look at, much less speak to. Xenohumans Expanded
races.name: radworld human

races.description: A Xenohuman genetically engineered both physically and neurologically to be the perfect worker at a very specific task. Bred and modified for complete and utter obedience at the whims of a now-unknown faction, they excel at most forms of skilled and simple labor, but learn new concepts quite slowly. Xenohumans Expanded
races.name: vatdrone
